<h2>The weather in March 2019</h2>
<br><br>
The first half of the month the weather in Central and Western Europe was dominated by low pressure systems, with regularly a lot of wind and precipitation. Southern Europe was mostly under influence of high pressure. The second half of the month the high pressure areas moved more northward, causing also dry and calm weather in the central part of Europe.
<br><br>
<h3>Temperature deviations and extremes</h3>
<br><br>
Due to the dominant westerly flow in North and Central Europe temperatures were above normal. Also southern Europe experienced above normal average and maximum temperatures under high pressure influence. Spain experienced colder than normal minimum temperatures due to cooling in clear nights.
