<h3>Cloudiness and Radiation</h3>
The division in high and low pressure systems between the northern and southern half of Europe can also be seen in the cloudiness and radiation figures. The southern half of Europe experienced around 30% more radiation than normal (Figure 14), whereas the northern part of Europe experienced less radiation and more clouds than normal.
